OL,3,C'It's barbaric': Woman with MS calls
OL,4,Cfor change to assisted dying law
OL,6,FMS is a lifelong condition that can
OL,7,Faffect the brain and spinal cord,
OL,8,Fcausing a wide range of possible
OL,9,Fsymptoms, including problems with
OL,10,Fvision, movement, or balance.
OL,12,FMs Jappie said it has left her with
OL,13,Fsevere mobility issues and she now has
OL,14,Fto take up to 15 tablets a day to
OL,15,Fmanage the pain.
OL,17,FShe said it would be "impossible" for
OL,18,Fher to travel to an assisted dying
OL,19,Fclinic in Switzerland on her own, but
OL,20,Fsaid she is worried her friends will
OL,21,Fbe punished if they help her.
